<h3 id=3D"ElectricalCircuits-PuttingItAllTogether">Putting It All Together<=
/h3>
<p>To analyze a simple resistive network:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Combine series/parallel</strong> resistors step by step.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Apply <strong>Ohm=E2=80=99s law</strong> to find total current or voltag=
e.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Use <strong>voltage division</strong> or <strong>current division</stron=
g> to find individual branch values.</p></li>
<li>
<p>If sources are awkward, perform a <strong>source transformation</strong>=
 to simplify.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>These four tools=E2=80=94<strong>series/parallel reduction, voltage divi=
sion, current division, and source transformation</strong>=E2=80=94form the=
 everyday toolkit for DC circuit analysis.</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<ol start=3D"4">
<li>
<p>Methods of analysis: nodal and mesh analysis</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Here=E2=80=99s a <strong>clear guide</strong> to the two fundamental cir=
cuit=E2=80=93analysis methods:</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ElectricalCircuits-1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3Nodal(Node-Voltage)Analysis=
">1=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Nodal (Node-Voltage) Analysis</h2>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Find the <strong>voltage at each node</strong> (r=
elative to a reference/ground) using <strong>KCL</strong>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"ElectricalCircuits-Steps">Steps</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Choose a reference node</strong> (ground).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Label voltages</strong> V1,V2,=E2=80=A6V_1, V_2, =E2=80=A6 at th=
e remaining nodes.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Write KCL</strong> at each non-reference node:</p>
<p><em>Sum of currents leaving a node =3D 0.</em></p></li>
<li>
<p>Express each branch current as (Vnode=E2=88=92Vneighbor)/R(V_\text{node}=
 - V_\text{neighbor})/R.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Solve the simultaneous equations.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<p><strong>Example</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">   10 V
(+) =E2=94=80=E2=94=80R1=3D2k=E2=94=80=E2=97=8F=E2=94=80R2=3D3k=E2=94=80(gr=
ound)
            |
           R3=3D6k
            |
         (ground)
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Let node voltage =3D V1V_1.</p></li>
<li>
<p>KCL at node:</p>
<p>V1=E2=88=92102000+V1=E2=88=9203000+V1=E2=88=9206000=3D0\frac{V_1 - 10}{2=
000} + \frac{V_1 - 0}{3000} + \frac{V_1 - 0}{6000} =3D 0</p></li>
<li>
<p>Solve:</p>
<p>V1(12000+13000+16000)=3D102000V_1 \left(\frac{1}{2000}+\frac{1}{3000}+\f=
rac{1}{6000}\right) =3D \frac{10}{2000}</p>
<p>=E2=87=92 V1=E2=89=882.7&nbsp;VV_1 =E2=89=88 2.7\ \text{V}.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"ElectricalCircuits-2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3Mesh(Loop-Current)Analysis"=
>2=EF=B8=8F=E2=83=A3 Mesh (Loop-Current) Analysis</h2>
<p><strong>Goal:</strong> Find the <strong>current in each independent loop=
</strong> using <strong>KVL</strong>.</p>
<h3 id=3D"ElectricalCircuits-Steps.1">Steps</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Identify meshes</strong> (smallest closed loops).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Assign a mesh current</strong> I1,I2,=E2=80=A6I_1, I_2, =E2=80=
=A6 clockwise or counter-clockwise.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Write KVL</strong> around each mesh:</p>
<p><em>Sum of voltage rises and drops =3D 0.</em></p></li>
<li>
<p>Shared components carry the algebraic difference of mesh currents.</p></=
li>
<li>
<p>Solve the linear equations.</p></li>
</ol>
<hr>
<p><strong>Example</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">   R1=
=3D4=CE=A9
 =E2=94=8C=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80R2=3D6=CE=A9=E2=94=
=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=90
 |               |
10V            5V
 |               |
 =E2=94=94=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80R3=3D8=CE=A9=E2=94=
=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=80=E2=94=98
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Two meshes: left (I=E2=82=81) and right (I=E2=82=82).</p></li>
<li>
<p>KVL:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Left: 10 =E2=88=92 4I=E2=82=81 =E2=88=92 6(I=E2=82=81 =E2=88=92 I=E2=82=
=82) =3D 0</p></li>
<li>
<p>Right: 5 =E2=88=92 8I=E2=82=82 =E2=88=92 6(I=E2=82=82 =E2=88=92 I=E2=82=
=81) =3D 0</p></li>
</ul></li>
